Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: The Landscape of the Law
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01jmxrx
Last Broadcast Date: Sat 7 Jul 2012
The historian Niall Ferguson delivers a lecture at Gresham College in the heart of legal London, addressing the relationship between the nature of law and economic success. He examines the rule of law in comparative terms, asking how far the common law's claims to superiority over other systems are credible. Are we living through a time of creeping legal degeneration in the English-speaking world? Producer: Jane Beresford. Show less